description: Under siege inside Megatron's floating fortress, the Maximals must protect the captive sparks against Megatron's final attack.
name: Endgame Part 1: The Downward Spiral

description: Horribly outnumbered, the Maximals make their last stand against Megatron and his Vehicon army.
name: Endgame Part 2: When Legends Fall

deck: Season 2 finale.
description: With the others Maximal's sparks taken by Megatron. The last two living Transformers on Cybertron, Optimus Primal and Megatron stage their final battle.
name: Endgame Part 3: Seeds of the Future

deck: First part of the three part mini-series.
description: In a constant war between the Autobots and the Decepticons on Cybertron has caused great hardship. Both need supplies, and select numbers from each side and intend to get them. In search of energy, the Autobots leave Cybertron and are pursued by the Decepticons.
name: More than Meets the Eye, Part 1

deck: Second part of the three part mini-series.
description: Things continue to progress; with the Decepticons on the move, and the Autobots gaining Spike and Sparkplug Witwicky as allies. The Decepticons continue raiding Earth's energy sources, including Sherman Dam and the Ruby Crystal Mines of Burma.
name: More than Meets the Eye, Part 2

deck: Final part in the three part mini-series.
description: Following the latest action, both sides are basically back to where they started. When an Autobot attempt to lure the Decepticons into a holographic trap fails, the villains succeed in gathering the energy they need, leaving the Autobots with only one chance to stop them returning to Cybertron. With a ship ready and Cybertron in great danger, an all-out battle between the Autobots and the Decepticons looms.
name: More than Meets the Eye, Part 3

deck: Who framed the Fantastic Four?
description:
The Fantastic Four are called upon to stop monsters menacing the coast, by order of President Bill Clinton. However, a shape-changing alien race known as the Skrulls are planning to take over the Earth and they are using a Skrull disguised as the President and the monsters as a mere distraction. Their master plan: To make the world believe that the Four have become vile, then take over!

Note: This episode is a direct adaptation of Fantastic Four Issue #2.
name: Incursion of the Skrulls

deck: Namor rises from the ocean floor!
description:
Namor is out to teach the people of Earth about how pollution can destroy the world. The family is hot on the Sub-Mariner's tail when he just kidnapped Sue to make her his queen of Atlantis. But, the warlord Krang is taking control of the Atlantean army and is wrecking up the city. It's up to the team and Namor's combined might to stop the fiend.

Note: This episode is a direct adaptation of Fantastic Four Issue #4.
name: Now Comes the Sub-Mariner

deck: The "Devourer of Worlds" has come to Earth!
description:
When the sky suddenly turn fiery red, the Human Torch is instantly blamed for the happening. Suddenly, an entity known as the Watcher came to Mr. Fantastic's laboratory to tell them of the coming of Galactus, a colossal being that consumes upon every planet for the satisfaction of his hunger. Now it's up to the team to stop Galactus, before he eats Earth and everyone in it.

Note: This episode is a direct adaptation and combination of Fantastic Four Issues #48 and #49.
name: The Silver Surfer and the Coming of Galactus: Part 1

deck: First episode.
description: After months in hiding, the Decepticons return and have a new method for moving energon cubes to Cybertron. A new space bridge could do that, but it has problems like possibly being fatal to whoever tries to go through it.
name: Transport to Oblivion

deck: Second episode. With Megatron assumed dead, Starscream seizes power and does things his way.
description: The Decepticons seek a powerful antimatter formula, and the Autobots with their new human ally Chip Chase try to stop them.
name: Roll for It

deck: Third episode. The Autobots prevent the Decepticons from harming a weapons factory, but at a heavy price: Optimus himself.
description: The Autobots must journey to Cybertron to retrieve a vital piece of technology to save the life of the critically wounded Optimus Prime.
name: Divide and Conquer

deck: Fourth episode.
description: While siphoning the Earth of its energy, the Decepticons uncover a long-lost colleague of Starscream.
name: Fire in the Sky

deck: Fifth episode. A little extra muscle in the Autobot ranks would certainly be welcome. Coincidentally, nearby dinosaur fossils provide the necessary means.
description: The Autobots create the Dinobots, but can barely control these new powerful warriors.
name: S.O.S. Dinobots

deck: Sixth episode. There is a crystal of massive power out there. Both sides become aware of it and the Decepticons reach it first.
description: The Decepticons uncover the Crystal of Power in Peru, and the Autobots resurrect Skyfire to stop them.
name: Fire on the Mountain
A Once in a Lifetime Chance
I Want to Know More About You

deck: When Optimus Prime appears to attack Agent Fowler, the Autobots discover MECH's ultimate plan.
description: M.E.C.H. produces a clone of Optimus Prime.
name: Nemesis Prime

deck: Agent Fowler has some explaining to do under the threat of military tribunal and Team Prime's termination.
description:
Agent Fowler is forced to explain recent events to his superior.

Flashback episode.
name: Grill

deck: Bulkhead is trapped on the Nemesis during an attempt on Megatron's life
description: Bulkhead accidentally becomes trapped on board the Nemesis while on a scouting mission.
name: Armada

deck: Megatron's attempt to repair the Nemesis has an unexpected side effect, forcing Raf, Jack, and Miko to put themselves in harm's way.
description: The Nemesis has crashed on a mountainside and its engines are badly damaged.
name: Flying Mind

deck: Arcee and Bumblebee go deep into New York's "underground" in an attempt to beat Megatron to the next four Iacon relics.
description: Having discovered the locations of four Iacon relics hidden across the globe, Team Prime splits up into small groups and head to each location simultaneously to retrieve them.
name: Tunnel Vision

deck: Zorro fights the henchmen of the county's corrupt politician in a working goldmine!
name: The Deadly Millstone
Who Do You Think You Are
A Hedgehog's Home is Her Castle

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 最悪の切り札! グルメ界の怪物 “ニトロ” (Saiaku no Kirifuda! Gurume-kai no Kaibutsu “Nitoro”)

The IGO's chances for victory take a serious hit when the Gourmet Corp. unleashes the horrifying monsters Nitro and the Scum Beasts!
name: Worst Trump Card! The Gourmet World Monster, 'Nitro'!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 死闘！ココVSグリンパーチ (Shitō! Koko VS Gurinpāchi)

Thanks to Komatsu’s super culinary skills, Coco and Toriko have the strength to carry on their battles with two of the Gourmet Corp.’s most powerful monsters!
name: Mortal Combat! Coco vs. Grinpatch!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 決闘！サニーVSトミーロッド (Kettō! Sanī VS Tomīroddo)

Sunny puts his heroic hair to the ultimate test in a bombastic battle with Tommyrod and his grotesque army of deadly insects!
name: Duel! Sunny vs. Tommyrod!

description: ARROW HUNTS DOWN SHRAPNEL — Oliver must tackle a new threat to the city when bombs start to go off in Starling City. Felicity (Emily Bett Rickards) discovers the person setting them off is Mark Sheffner (guest star Sean Maher), a man who goes by the nickname Shrapnel. Arrow discovers Shrapnel’s next target is Sebastian Blood’s (guest star Kevin Alejandro) “Unity Rally” and tries to talk the alderman out of hosting it, but he refuses. Arrow sets off to stop the bombing, but Shrapnel tricks him and traps him in a bomb-laced antique store where he is unable to move without setting off the device. While Felicity helps Oliver, Diggle (David Ramsey) races to the plaza to find the bomb before it goes off. Meanwhile, Roy (Colton Haynes) continues to hide his new strength from Thea (Willa Holland) but, after she witnesses his super strength in action at the rally, she demands answers. Laurel’s (Katie Cassidy) suspicions about Sebastian grow stronger once she learns that he grew up with Cyrus Gold, the man who killed Lance’s (Paul Blackthorne) partner. After Donner (guest Star Dylan Bruce) refuses to help her investigate, she turns to Arrow (Stephen Amell) for help.
name: Blast Radius

deck: A long walk.
description: Bill steal a bone and come back to his home with it, when the parents of bill see that Bill have made a crime they order him to bring back what he have stolen.
name: Une longue marche

description: A Major Turnaround! Luffy's Angry Iron Fist Strikes! (大逆転! 炸裂ルフィ怒りの鉄, Dai-gyakuten! Sakuretsu Rufi Ikari no Tekken)
name: A Major Turnaround! Luffy's Angry Iron Fist Strikes!

deck: Coulson and May uncover startling information about Skye’s past, while the team is swept into a storm at S.H.I.E.L.D. Academy
name: Seeds

deck: The Fantastic Four continue their battle against Galactus!
description:
Galactus is here! The Watcher has tried to be diplomatic with the monster to not devour our world, but it did not work. Galactus's machine is in near completion. Time is running out for both Earth and the Fantastic Four. Meanwhile, the Silver Surfer has finally recovered and must make a tough decision. Will he obey his master and allow Earth to be consumed, or will he stand in his way and save us?

Note: This episode is a direct adaptation and combination of Fantastic Four Issues #48 until #50.
name: The Silver Surfer and the Coming of Galactus: Part 2

deck: The Super-Skrull unleashes mayhem!
description:
Remember the Skrulls? Yeah, those face-changing aliens who framed the Four a few episodes ago. Well, there back and this time they're taking things up a notch. They have just built a device that will grant a Skrull with powers carried by each team member. When they have deployed their "Super-Skrull", the Fantastic Four go on a fight to the finish. But how can they defeat an enemy who has all of their powers?

Note: This episode is a direct adaptation of Fantastic Four Issue #18.
name: Superskrull

deck: Doctor Doom captured the team!
description:
Doctor Doom was able to disarm the Fantastic Four in there headquarters. He sends them into his airship then into his castle. Doom invited the Invisible Woman for dinner and accepted it in order to learn more about him. Surrounded by Doombots and trapped on a nearly isolated and decaying castle, Mr. Fantastic, Thing and Human Torch must find a way to escape Doom's clutches and save Sue.

Note: This, including it's following episodes are all direct adaptations of Fantastic Four Issue #5.
name: The Mask of Doom: Part 1

deck:
Art Carney as The Archer
Cliffhanger: The Dynamic Duo are tied to stakes and The Archer and his men, on horseback, are about to run them down with lances
name: Shoot a Crooked Arrow

deck: Batman and Robin escape using the Batsprings concealed in their boots.
name: Walk the Straight and Narrow

deck: On a mission, to save Susan Storm from the maniacal Doctor Doom!
description:
Doctor Doom tells his origin story to the Invisible Woman. We learn that he is looking for a cure for his long messed-up face. Elsewhere, Reed, Johnny and Ben are attempting to avoid Doom's death traps and must live long enough to fight Doom. But when this Doctor Doom is actually a Doombot in disguise, the three are forced to go on a time travelling adventure to retrieve a mysterious Greek coffin.

Note: This, including it's past and future episode are all direct adaptations of Fantastic Four Issue #5.
name: The Mask of Doom: Part 2

deck: Iron Man must stop Ivan Vanko, a vengeful astronaut that was abandoned by his crew two years ago inside the massive Crimson Dynamo armor, and has crash-landed back on Earth, seeking revenge.
